Random Visualizations
-------------------------

Using Chart.js, randomize different chart types for designers and developers to use to quickly prototype solutions. Add the ability to quickly download an image:

Select chart type (table, pie, bar, doughnut, line, map)
Select data variables, sets, etc?
Randomize data
Customize chart colors, and other options
Download image
Save Random Settings > folder > filename (have to create account)

Also map data, and other types of data not supported with chart.js


Random Data Generating API
--------------------------------
https://randomuser.me/
https://randomapi.com/
https://api.random.org/json-rpc/1/
https://www.mockaroo.com/api/docs

Visualization/Charts API
http://www.chartjs.org/docs/


Domain Name Examples
randomvisualizations.*
randomcharts
randomchartjs
loremdata
randomdata.co



Random Data Generation: 
Variables
1. Chart Title, string, ex: "My Chart" <-- not needed.

2. Minimum Value, int, ex: 10
3. Max Value: int, ex: 20,000
4. Categories/Items: int, ex: 3 --> top level category
5. Items per category: int, ex: 2 --> items per category 

6. X Axis Name: string, ex: "Monday"
7. Y Axis Name: string, ex: "Dollars"
9. Category Item Names: string, ex: "Sales", "Loss"
